gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Timberwolves 118, Clippers 100
gameRecap.excerpt: The Timberwolves defeated the Clippers, 118-100. Anthony Edwards led the way for the Timberwolves with a game-high 37 points, along with eight rebounds and four assists, while Nickeil Alexander-Walker added a season-high 28 points (5-6 3pt. FG) in the victory. Paul George tallied 22 points, three rebounds and three assists for the Clippers in the losing effort. The Timberwolves improve to 45-21 on the season, while the Clippers fall to 41-23.
